title: Macros/choice

\relink choice item:reference
\define choice(type, item) //$type$ of choice//: ''{{$item$}}''
<<print-before-this>>

The choice macro takes a reference for its second parameter called ''item''.

This global macro relies on an inline definition using the `\relink` pragma to declare its ''item'' parameter as something that should be relinked. See [[Inline Declarations]] for more information.
